<Layout title="Responsive Image Examples">
  <main>
    <section class="container mx-auto px-4 py-10">
      <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-8">Responsive Image Components</h1>

      <div class="mb-16">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-4">Basic ResponsiveImage</h2>
        <p class="mb-4">
          This component automatically creates responsive images with multiple
          formats and sizes
        </p>

        <div class="border border-gray-300 p-4 rounded-lg">
          <ResponsiveImage
            src={sampleImagePath}
            alt="Sample landscape image"
            width={1200}
            height={800}
            loading="eager"
            format="webp"
            breakpoints={[640, 768, 1024, 1280]}
          />
        </div>

        <p class="mt-4 text-sm text-gray-600">
          The ResponsiveImage component above generates optimized versions at
          different breakpoints (640px, 768px, 1024px, 1280px) and serves them
          with appropriate srcset and sizes attributes.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="mb-16">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-4">
          CMSImage with Aspect Ratio Control
        </h2>
        <p class="mb-4">
          This component is specialized for CMS-sourced images with aspect ratio
          control and focal point
        </p>

        <div class="border border-gray-300 p-4 rounded-lg">
          <CMSImage
            src={sampleImagePath}
            alt="Image from CMS with aspect ratio control"
            aspectRatio="16:9"
            focalPoint="center"
            placeholder={true}
            wrapperClass="max-w-2xl mx-auto"
          />
        </div>

        <p class="mt-4 text-sm text-gray-600">
          The CMSImage component maintains a 16:9 aspect ratio regardless of
          screen size and optimizes loading with placeholder images for better
          user experience.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="mb-16">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-4">
          Background Image with Art Direction
        </h2>
        <p class="mb-4">
          The BackgroundImage component supports different image sources for
          different screen sizes
        </p>

        <div class="border border-gray-300 rounded-lg overflow-hidden">
          <BackgroundImage
            src={sampleImagePath}
            mobileSrc={sampleMobileImagePath}
            alt="Background image example"
            overlayColor="rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.4)"
            fixed={false}
            height={400}
          >
            <div
              class="flex items-center justify-center h-full text-center p-6"
            >
              <div class="text-white">
                <h3 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-3">Responsive Background</h3>
                <p class="max-w-lg mx-auto">
                  This background image automatically adapts to different screen
                  sizes, with art direction for optimal display across devices.
                </p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </BackgroundImage>
        </div>

        <p class="mt-4 text-sm text-gray-600">
          The BackgroundImage component above uses different images for mobile
          and desktop views, and includes a semi-transparent overlay with
          centered content.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="mb-16">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-4">Image Optimization Features</h2>
        <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2">
          <li>
            Automatic WebP and AVIF format generation with fallbacks for older
            browsers
          </li>
          <li>Responsive sizing with appropriate dimensions for each device</li>
          <li>Lazy loading for images below the fold</li>
          <li>Blur-up loading effect for better perceived performance</li>
          <li>LQIP (Low-Quality Image Placeholders) during loading</li>
          <li>Art direction support for different screen sizes</li>
          <li>Aspect ratio maintenance to prevent layout shifts</li>
          <li>Focal point control for better cropping</li>
          <li>Domain allowlisting for security</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>
</Layout>

